fulltitle: Part 2/Kenny Barron:  Classical music and "the swamp of Jazz"
description: In part 2 of an in-depth interview, maestro Kenny Barron talks about how Jazz is perceived in relation to Classical music.  Honored by The National Endowment for the Arts as a 2010 Jazz Master, Mr. Barron has worked with such legendary figures as Dizzy Gillespie, Stan Getz, Roy  Haynes, Lee Morgan, James Moody, Freddie Hubbard, Stanley Turrentine, Milt Jackson, Buddy Rich, Yusef Lateef, and Terence Blanchard, among others. He has also been the leader on more than forty albums, and counting!
title: Part 2/Kenny Barron:  Classical music and "the swamp of Jazz"
